  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Clinical performance of the Meritas Troponin I test</measure>
    <time_frame>24-hours</time_frame>
    <description>Clinical performance indicators (Sensitivity, Specificity, Positive Predictive Value (PPV) and Negative Predictive Value (NPV) and their respective 95 % confidence intervals (CIs) will be calculated for the quantitative determination of cardiac troponin I (cTnI) for use as an aid in the diagnosis of myocardial infarction (MI)</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Prognostic capability of sponsor's Meritas Troponin I to predict mortality (all-cause death) and cardiac events (i.e., MI, cardiac death).</measure>
    <time_frame>1 year</time_frame>
    <description>Kaplan-Meier survival curves and risk ratios. A multivariate Cox proportional model with known risk factors as covariates in addition to the Troponin test result will be included in the data analysis</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
